<h1><i class="fa fa-mobile"></i>Running on iOS</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/getting-started"><i class="fa fa-bicycle"></i>Getting Started</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-mobile"></i>Running on iOS</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p>If you have an Apple iPhone or iPad, then we recommend that you run <%= application.name %> as described below. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-home"></i>Running from the Home Screen</h2>
			<p>There are two ways to run <%= application.name %>. </p>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<p><label>Run from your Web Browser</label><br />You can start your web browser (Safari, Chrome, or Firefox) and then navigate to the <%= application.name %> web site. </p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<p><label>Run from the Home Screen</label><br />You can create an icon on your home screen that launches the <%= application.name %> web application. </p>

					<div class="figure row">
						<div class="figure col-xs-12 col-sm-6" style="float:none">
							<a href="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/app-on-home-screen.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="<%= application.name %> on the Home Screen"><img src="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/app-on-home-screen.png" /></a>
							<div class="caption"><%= application.name %> on the Home Screen</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</li>
			</ol>

			<p>We recommend that you run <%= application.name %> from your home screen rather than from a web browser for the following reasons: </p>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<p><label>Easier and quicker to launch</label><br />When <%= application.name %> has been added to your home screen, you can run <%= application.name %> by simply clicking on the <%= application.name %> icon rather than starting your web browser and then going to the web site.  One step is easier than two. </p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<p><label>Uses the full screen</label><br />When you run <%= application.name %> from the home screen, it will take up the entire screen rather than using the top part of the screen for the web browser's address bar. This gives you a significantly larger area of screen space to work with, particularly on small devices like the iPhone SE. </p>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-plus"></i>Adding <%= application.name %> to your Home Screen</h2>
			<p>To add <%= application.name %> to your home screen, perform the following actions. </p>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<h3>Open <%= application.name %> web site in Safari</h3>
					<p>Start your Safari web browser and navigate to the <%= application.name %> web site (<a href="<%= location.hostname %>"><%= location.hostname %></a>). </p>

					<div class="figure row">
						<div class="figure col-xs-12 col-sm-6" style="float:none">
							<a href="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/app-in-safari.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="<%= application.name %> in Safari"><img src="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/app-in-safari.png" /></a>
							<div class="caption"><%= application.name %> in Safari</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Open Web Page Options</h3>
					<p>Click the middle icon on the bottom toolbar in Safari to open the web page options. </p>

					<div class="figure row">
						<div class="figure col-xs-12 col-sm-6" style="float:none">
							<a href="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/web-page-options.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Web Page Options"><img src="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/web-page-options.png" /></a>
							<div class="caption">Web Page Options</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Add to Home Screen</h3>
					<p>On the web page options screen, click on the "Add to Home Screen" button.  Shorten the name and then click the "done" button.  You should now see <%= application.name %> on your home screen. </p>

					<div class="figure row">
						<div class="figure col-xs-12 col-sm-6" style="float:none">
							<a href="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/add-to-home-screen.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Add to Home Screen"><img src="images/help/getting-started/running-on-ios/add-to-home-screen.png" /></a>
							<div class="caption">Add to Home Screen</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>